
I. Installation
/!\ WARNING :
Before doing anything, you have to active Universe and Multiverse repositories. If you don't, the installation script won't work.
Here is a tutorial : http://www.psychocats.net/ubuntu/sources.php.

Here are the commands you have to run in order to install semantic-ruby (take care of being in the root directory : semantic-ruby/) :

  $ sudo apt-get install ruby-full build-essential
  $ sudo apt-get install libdb4.2-dev rubygems
  $ sudo ln -s $PWD/.semantic-rubyInstall/linkparser/link-grammar-4.4.1/link-grammar/.libs/liblink-grammar.so.4 /usr/lib/liblink-grammar.so.4
  $ sudo ln -s $PWD/.semantic-rubyInstall/wordnet-0.0.5/ruby-wordnet/ /usr/share/ruby-wordnet
  $ sudo gem install activesupport
  $ cd .semantic-rubyInstall/linkparser/link-grammar-4.4.1/
  $ ./configure
  $ make
  $ sudo make install
  $ cd ../../bdb-0.6.5
  $ sudo make install

And that's it, you can run semantic-ruby simply by typing :
  
  $ ruby semantic-ruby.rb

If you have troubles installing semantic-ruby, please send us a mail, we will reply as soon as possible.

